1
00:00:04,070 --> 00:00:04,900
Hi!

2
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:06,550
- Hey! - Hi!

3
00:00:07,050 --> 00:00:10,240
- How was the honeymoon? - Oh, incredible!

4
00:00:10,570 --> 00:00:13,210
Champagne, candle-lit dinners,

5
00:00:13,260 --> 00:00:14,900
moonlight walks on the beach.

6
00:00:14,950 --> 00:00:16,710
It was so romantic.

7
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:18,880
- Where's Mike? - He's at the doctor.

8
00:00:18,930 --> 00:00:20,830
He didn't poop while we were there.

9
00:00:23,380 --> 00:00:25,430
I'm glad you're back. I need your help.

10
00:00:25,430 --> 00:00:26,520
Oh, why, what's up?

11
00:00:26,570 --> 00:00:27,900
I have an audition for this play,

12
00:00:27,950 --> 00:00:29,930
and I have to speak French...

13
00:00:29,980 --> 00:00:31,360
...which, according to my resume,

14
00:00:31,410 --> 00:00:32,620
I'm fluent in.

15
00:00:33,420 --> 00:00:35,910
Joey, you shouldn't lie on your resume.

16
00:00:35,960 --> 00:00:37,840
Yeah, you really shouldn't.

17
00:00:37,890 --> 00:00:38,450
By the way,

18
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:40,730
how was that yearlong dig in Cairo?

19
00:00:42,510 --> 00:00:43,820
It was okay.

20
00:00:45,470 --> 00:00:47,330
I did not know you spoke French.

21
00:00:51,790 --> 00:00:53,310
You're so sexy.

22
00:00:54,330 --> 00:00:55,260
Well, so will you help me?

23
00:00:55,310 --> 00:00:56,310
I really wanna be in this play.

24
00:00:56,360 --> 00:00:57,060
Sure.

25
00:00:59,730 --> 00:01:00,860
Seriously, stop it.

26
00:01:00,910 --> 00:01:01,920
I'm gonna jump on you.

27
00:01:03,770 --> 00:01:05,910
《老友记》第十季第十三集 乔伊说法语

28
00:01:44,570 --> 00:01:45,280
- Hey. - Hi.

29
00:01:45,770 --> 00:01:47,070
Why are you wearing my apron?

30
00:01:48,860 --> 00:01:50,320
I'm making cookies for Erica.

31
00:01:50,370 --> 00:01:52,210
We have to leave soon.

32
00:01:52,260 --> 00:01:53,410
Her plane comes in in about an hour.

33
00:01:53,460 --> 00:01:54,560
When she gets here,

34
00:01:54,610 --> 00:01:57,080
is it okay if I introduce you two as my wife...

35
00:01:57,130 --> 00:01:59,450
...and the woman who's carrying my child?

36
00:02:01,070 --> 00:02:01,910
No?

37
00:02:03,090 --> 00:02:04,060
Divorce?

38
00:02:06,290 --> 00:02:07,490
- Hey. - Hey.

39
00:02:07,540 --> 00:02:09,300
You know where Rachel is?

40
00:02:09,350 --> 00:02:10,590
No, we haven't haven't seen her since morning.

41
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:11,800
It's unbelievable.

42
00:02:11,850 --> 00:02:12,690
She was supposed to meet me

43
00:02:12,740 --> 00:02:14,160
a half-hour ago with Emma.

44
00:02:14,570 --> 00:02:15,870
- Hey! - Hey!

45
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:17,360
These are for Erica!

46
00:02:17,410 --> 00:02:19,200
She's gonna eat all those cookies?

47
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,180
Well, I want the baby to come out

48
00:02:21,230 --> 00:02:22,660
all cute and fat!

49
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:26,860
So why is Erica coming to visit?

50
00:02:26,910 --> 00:02:28,490
We wanna get to know her better.

51
00:02:28,540 --> 00:02:30,110
And she's never been to New York,

52
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:31,920
so she wants to see the tourist spots:

53
00:02:31,970 --> 00:02:34,040
Statue of Liberty, Empire State Building.

54
00:02:34,090 --> 00:02:36,010
Oh, those places! There's always so many people,

55
00:02:36,060 --> 00:02:38,310
and they're being corralled like cattle.

56
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:42,030
And, you know, there's always some idiot who goes, "Moo."

57
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:44,630
Well, if it annoys you so much,

58
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,030
then why do you do it?

59
00:02:48,420 --> 00:02:50,730
Oh, hi. Hi. Thanks for showing up

60
00:02:50,730 --> 00:02:51,620
30 minutes late.

61
00:02:51,670 --> 00:02:52,220
Ross.

62
00:02:52,270 --> 00:02:54,270
No, I'm sure you have a great excuse.

63
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,760
What was it, a hair appointment?

64
00:02:55,810 --> 00:02:57,240
A mani-pedi?

65
00:02:57,290 --> 00:02:59,030
Barneys:纽约时尚精品店

66
00:02:57,290 --> 00:02:59,030
Was there a sale at Barneys?

67
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,900
My father had a heart attack.

68
00:03:02,540 --> 00:03:04,390
While I was at Barneys.

69
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:09,140
- Oh, my God, Rach. - Honey?

70
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:11,770
- I'm so sorry. - Is he okay?

71
00:03:11,820 --> 00:03:13,270
Yeah, he's gonna be fine,

72
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:14,660
but he's heavily sedated.

73
00:03:14,710 --> 00:03:16,870
Okay, I'm gonna go to Long lsland with you.

74
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:18,470
I mean, you can't be alone right now.

75
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:21,330
No, come on, I'm totally okay.

76
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:23,540
I don't need you to come.

77
00:03:24,110 --> 00:03:26,280
I can totally handle this on my own.

78
00:03:26,330 --> 00:03:29,270
Still, still, let me come for me.

79
00:03:30,370 --> 00:03:32,880
Okay. If you really need to.

80
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,710
I bet someone could use

81
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:36,840
one of Monica's freshly baked cookies.

82
00:03:36,890 --> 00:03:38,180
Oh, I really could.

83
00:03:46,510 --> 00:03:48,480
All right, it seems pretty simple.

84
00:03:48,530 --> 00:03:50,800
Your first line is, "My name is Claude."

85
00:03:50,850 --> 00:03:52,800
So just repeat after me.

86
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:03,130
- Well, let's try it again. - Okay.

87
00:04:10,220 --> 00:04:11,660
It's not...

88
00:04:12,380 --> 00:04:14,020
...quite what I'm saying.

89
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:17,890
Really? Sounds exactly the same to me.

90
00:04:18,670 --> 00:04:20,500
- It does, really? - Yeah.

91
00:04:21,270 --> 00:04:22,810
- Let's just try it again. - Okay.

92
00:04:22,860 --> 00:04:24,750
- Really listen. - Got it.

93
00:04:36,890 --> 00:04:39,380
- Hey, you guys! - Hi.

94
00:04:39,430 --> 00:04:41,800
I want you to meet someone really special.

95
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:45,450
Phoebe, this is Erica. And this is the baby!

96
00:04:46,140 --> 00:04:48,550
- Joey, Erica, baby. - Hi.

97
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:51,450
Everyone, Erica! Baby!

98
00:04:52,030 --> 00:04:53,920
Monica. Calm. Self.

99
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:56,640
- Hey, sit down. - Thank you.

100
00:04:56,690 --> 00:04:58,190
It's really nice to meet you guys.

101
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,720
I can't believe I'm here.

102
00:04:59,770 --> 00:05:02,230
Well, welcome to New York City, or should I say:

103
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:04,070
不知所云的法语

104
00:05:06,450 --> 00:05:07,920
Why would you say that?

105
00:05:09,370 --> 00:05:11,520
Okay. What are you gonna be doing today?

106
00:05:11,570 --> 00:05:13,310
Well, I wanna see everything!

107
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:16,520
Times Square, Coney lsland, Rockefeller Center.

108
00:05:16,570 --> 00:05:17,560
Oh, you know what you should do?

109
00:05:17,610 --> 00:05:18,600
You should walk to

110
00:05:18,650 --> 00:05:19,880
the top of the Statue of Liberty.

111
00:05:19,930 --> 00:05:22,660
- Oh, yeah, let's do that. - Great.

112
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:25,120
This baby better be really good.

113
00:05:31,010 --> 00:05:32,420
Hi. Excuse me,

114
00:05:32,470 --> 00:05:33,340
I'm here to see my father.

115
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:34,260
My name is Rachel Green.

116
00:05:34,310 --> 00:05:35,650
And I'm Dr. Ross Geller.

117
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:37,680
Ross, please, this is a hospital.

118
00:05:37,730 --> 00:05:39,720
Doctor:医生也是博士的意思

119
00:05:37,730 --> 00:05:39,720
That actually means something here.

120
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:42,570
- So can we please go in? - Absolutely.

121
00:05:42,620 --> 00:05:44,820
Rach, I think I'm gonna wait out here...

122
00:05:44,870 --> 00:05:47,420
...because my throat is feeling a little scratchy.

123
00:05:47,470 --> 00:05:48,770
I don't wanna infect him.

124
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:50,780
Ross, please. Don't be so scared of him.

125
00:05:50,830 --> 00:05:53,410
I am not scared of him. I'm really sick.

126
00:05:53,460 --> 00:05:54,400
He's under sedation,

127
00:05:54,450 --> 00:05:55,490
so he's pretty much out.

128
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:56,680
I'm feeling better.

129
00:06:00,330 --> 00:06:02,060
Oh, my God.

130
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:06,970
That ear and nose hair trimmer I got him

131
00:06:07,020 --> 00:06:08,930
was just money down the drain, huh?

132
00:06:10,330 --> 00:06:11,470
Ms. Green?

133
00:06:11,610 --> 00:06:13,060
Your father's doctor's on the phone

134
00:06:13,110 --> 00:06:14,160
if you'd like to speak to him.

135
00:06:14,210 --> 00:06:15,740
Oh, great. Are you gonna be okay?

136
00:06:15,910 --> 00:06:18,010
He's unconscious. We'll be just fine.

137
00:06:18,060 --> 00:06:18,690
Okay.

138
00:06:56,860 --> 00:06:59,120
- Did the TV wake you? - No.

139
00:06:59,590 --> 00:07:01,750
When you put your feet up on my bed,

140
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,660
you tugged on my catheter.

141
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:12,580
What are you doing here, Geller?

142
00:07:12,630 --> 00:07:13,830
Well, I came with Rachel,

143
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:15,700
who should be back any second.

144
00:07:16,860 --> 00:07:18,050
So, what's new?

145
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:20,280
Oh, I had a little heart attack.

146
00:07:21,230 --> 00:07:22,830
Right. Is it painful?

147
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:24,150
What, the heart attack

148
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:25,470
or sitting here talking to you?

149
00:07:27,470 --> 00:07:30,330
Let's see if we can get that Rachel back in here.

150
00:07:30,730 --> 00:07:32,430
So, what's new with you?

151
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:34,710
Knocked up any more of my daughters lately?

152
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:36,920
Nope. Just the one. Rach!

153
00:07:43,330 --> 00:07:44,460
No!

154
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:48,040
Okay, maybe if we just break it down.

155
00:07:48,540 --> 00:07:51,460
Okay, let's try it one syllable at a time.

156
00:07:51,510 --> 00:07:53,200
Okay, so repeat after me.

157
00:07:57,660 --> 00:07:59,070
Great! Okay, faster.

158
00:08:07,050 --> 00:08:09,450
Okay, it's too hard. I can't teach you.

159
00:08:09,450 --> 00:08:10,070
What are you doing?

160
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,050
I have to go

161
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,530
before I put your head through a wall.

162
00:08:12,580 --> 00:08:15,020
Don't go, I need you!

163
00:08:15,070 --> 00:08:16,690
My audition is tomorrow!

164
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:35,950
Hey. I was gonna make us some dinner...

165
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,580
...but all I found in your dad's fridge

166
00:08:37,630 --> 00:08:39,340
was bacon and heavy cream.

167
00:08:40,670 --> 00:08:41,470
I think we solved

168
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:42,950
the mystery of the heart attack.

169
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:44,760
Did you call your parents?

170
00:08:44,810 --> 00:08:46,140
Oh, yeah. Emma's doing great.

171
00:08:46,190 --> 00:08:47,360
Oh, good.

172
00:08:50,770 --> 00:08:52,910
- What? - I just can't believe...

173
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:54,700
...I'm in Rachel Green's room.

174
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:56,650
What do you mean?

175
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:58,250
You've been in my room before.

176
00:08:58,420 --> 00:09:00,030
Yeah, sure, right.

177
00:09:01,370 --> 00:09:03,560
Like I'd ever be in Rachel Green's room.

178
00:09:03,610 --> 00:09:04,810
Okay, I gotta tell you,

179
00:09:04,860 --> 00:09:06,570
it's really weird when you use my whole name.

180
00:09:07,610 --> 00:09:08,590
Sorry.

181
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:12,600
- You okay? - Yeah.

182
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,990
- Yeah, you had a rough day. - Yeah.

183
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:17,800
It's just so weird seeing him like that, you know?

184
00:09:17,850 --> 00:09:19,360
I mean, he's a doctor.

185
00:09:19,410 --> 00:09:22,130
You don't expect doctors to get sick.

186
00:09:22,540 --> 00:09:23,960
But we do.

187
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:30,450
He's gonna be okay, Rach.

188
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,770
I don't want him to wake up alone.

189
00:09:36,820 --> 00:09:37,960
I should go to the hospital.

190
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:39,900
What? No, no. Hey, hey, look.

191
00:09:39,950 --> 00:09:40,410
What?

192
00:09:40,460 --> 00:09:42,080
They gave him a lot of medication.

193
00:09:42,130 --> 00:09:44,050
He wouldn't even know if you were there.

194
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:46,610
We'll go see him first thing in the morning. Ok?

195
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:48,060
Really? I shouldn't feel guilty?

196
00:09:48,110 --> 00:09:49,060
No-- God, hey.

197
00:09:49,110 --> 00:09:51,580
Rach, you've been an amazing daughter, okay?

198
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:53,600
Right now you need to get some rest.

199
00:09:53,610 --> 00:09:55,080
Okay, maybe you're right.

200
00:09:55,950 --> 00:09:57,090
Good night.

201
00:09:59,350 --> 00:10:00,780
Wait, wait, wait.

202
00:10:02,010 --> 00:10:03,370
Would you stay here

203
00:10:03,420 --> 00:10:04,880
with me for a little while?

204
00:10:06,180 --> 00:10:07,790
- Sure. - Okay.

205
00:10:09,350 --> 00:10:11,700
Thank you for coming with me today.

206
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:13,120
Oh, of course.

207
00:10:13,170 --> 00:10:15,810
Rachel Green is very happy you're in her room.

208
00:10:17,740 --> 00:10:19,800
Me too. Come here.

209
00:10:21,730 --> 00:10:24,140
I just don't wanna be alone tonight.

210
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:26,320
Okay, well,

211
00:10:26,570 --> 00:10:29,600
I can maybe grab a sleeping bag or--

212
00:10:44,950 --> 00:10:46,350
No, Rach!

213
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:48,520
I'm sorry,

214
00:10:48,570 --> 00:10:51,630
I just don't think this is a good idea.

215
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:53,880
Well, we won't know that until we do it,

216
00:10:53,930 --> 00:10:54,780
will we?

217
00:10:54,830 --> 00:10:56,450
No, look, uh.

218
00:10:57,190 --> 00:11:00,040
You are upset about your father,

219
00:11:00,090 --> 00:11:01,680
and you're feeling vulnerable...

220
00:11:01,730 --> 00:11:03,350
...and I just don't feel it

221
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,150
would be right.

222
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,520
I feel like I'd be, you know,

223
00:11:05,570 --> 00:11:06,680
taking advantage of you.

224
00:11:06,730 --> 00:11:07,800
What--? Taking advantage?

225
00:11:07,850 --> 00:11:10,740
I am giving you the advantage. Enjoy!

226
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:14,850
Look, I'm sure it would be great...

227
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:18,210
...but I think one of us has to be thinking clearly.

228
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:20,190
So I'm gonna go.

229
00:11:25,790 --> 00:11:27,100
Okay.

230
00:11:31,070 --> 00:11:32,710
I'll see you in the morning.

231
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:37,500
I haven't had sex in four months.

232
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:39,130
I should get a medal for that!

233
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,430
Thanks so much for taking me to all those places.

234
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,490
I had a great time.

235
00:11:49,540 --> 00:11:50,440
I'm glad.

236
00:11:50,490 --> 00:11:52,410
Listen, I wanna apologize about Chandler, though.

237
00:11:52,460 --> 00:11:54,280
I just did not see this coming.

238
00:11:54,330 --> 00:11:56,540
New York is awesome!

239
00:11:59,130 --> 00:12:00,340
What is with you?

240
00:12:00,390 --> 00:12:02,280
You know, I've been to these places before...

241
00:12:02,330 --> 00:12:03,990
...but I've never really seen them.

242
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:05,890
Yeah, you miss a lot when you're mooing.

243
00:12:08,040 --> 00:12:10,040
Thank you for showing me around.

244
00:12:10,090 --> 00:12:11,600
Oh, it was our pleasure.

245
00:12:11,650 --> 00:12:13,750
We're so much enjoying getting to know you.

246
00:12:13,950 --> 00:12:16,360
Well, if there's anything else you wanna know....

247
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:20,720
Okay.

248
00:12:22,070 --> 00:12:23,220
Can we ask you some questions

249
00:12:23,270 --> 00:12:24,460
about the father?

250
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:26,440
Oh, sure. Yeah.

251
00:12:26,890 --> 00:12:29,020
Well, he was my high-school boyfriend,

252
00:12:29,070 --> 00:12:31,420
captain of the football team, really cute.

253
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:34,440
Got a scholarship and went to college.

254
00:12:34,490 --> 00:12:35,550
That's great.

255
00:12:36,770 --> 00:12:39,490
Yeah, it's almost definitely him.

256
00:12:41,610 --> 00:12:43,010
How's that, now?

257
00:12:43,670 --> 00:12:46,280
Well, there's a chance it's another guy.

258
00:12:46,580 --> 00:12:49,740
I mean, I've only ever been with two guys...

259
00:12:50,330 --> 00:12:52,110
...but they sort of overlapped.

260
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:54,930
So, what does the other guy do?

261
00:12:54,980 --> 00:12:56,460
Does he go to college too?

262
00:12:56,510 --> 00:12:57,890
No, he's in prison.

263
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:03,700
Was he falsely accused of something?

264
00:13:05,060 --> 00:13:06,490
No.

265
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:08,950
He killed his father with a shovel.

266
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:13,050
Other than that, he's a great guy.

267
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:15,400
I'll bet his dad doesn't think so.

268
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:27,160
- Are you awake? - Of course I'm awake.

269
00:13:27,210 --> 00:13:29,370
Assume from now on that I'm always awake.

270
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:34,000
All right, we don't know that it's him.

271
00:13:34,050 --> 00:13:35,520
I mean, it could be the football guy.

272
00:13:35,570 --> 00:13:36,700
